{
  "texts": [
    "The maxim of quality pertains to the truthfulness and honesty of the response, specifically:",
    "(1) The response should be factual and supported by adequate evidence whenever possible.",
    "(2) The response should accurately reflect what the speaker knows to be true.",
    "One of the most significant issues in current language models is their tendency to hallucinate (Ji et al., 2023; Zhang et al., 2023; Xu et al., 2024).",
    "Hallucinations in language models are primarily understood to arise from both data issues -incorrect referencing (Wang, 2020) and inappropriate data handling (Lee et al., 2021) -and training issues -imperfect representations (Aralikatte et al., 2021), erroneous decoding (Tian et al., 2019), and a variety of knowledge biases (Wang and Sennrich, 2020; Longpre et al., 2021)."
  ]
}